entries.summary: FEX-Emu is a fast Linux-based x86 and x86-64 emulator designed to run user-mode applications. This emulator could be useful for developers, researchers, or anyone interested in running legacy x86 software on modern systems without the overhead of a full virtual machine. The webpage likely provides details about the emulator's features, performance, and potential use cases.
